text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia singula is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Juliflorae. It is native to an area in the Goldfields-Esperance and Wheatbelt regions of Western Australia.The shrub typically grows to a height of 0.35 to 2 metres (1 to 7 ft). It blooms from August to October producing yellow flowers.
